---
import RedSectionHeader from "../common/RedSectionHeader.astro";
---

<section class="py-20 bg-gray-50" id="pillar-vs-insurance">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <RedSectionHeader
            title="3rd Pillar vs. Pure Life Insurance"
            className="mb-12"
        />

        <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-700 max-w-none">
            <p class="mb-12 text-xl leading-relaxed">
                A common point of confusion for expats is the difference between
                saving in a 3rd Pillar (which can be a life insurance policy)
                and buying pure Risk Life Insurance. They serve completely
                different masters.
            </p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 mb-16">
                <!-- 3rd Pillar -->
                <div
                    class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border-t-4 border-red-600"
                >
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                        Perspective 1: The 3rd Pillar
                    </h3>
                    <span
                        class="inline-block bg-red-100 text-red-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded mb-4 font-bold"
                        >WEALTH ACCUMULATION</span
                    >
                    <p class="text-sm mb-4">
                        <strong>Primary Goal:</strong> To make you rich(er) at retirement.
                    </p>
                    <ul class="text-sm list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                        <li>
                            <strong>Mechanism:</strong> You put money in, it grows,
                            you take it out.
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Tax:</strong> Deductible contributions.</li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Payout:</strong> Based on YOUR contributions +
                            growth.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Use Case:</strong> Everyone who wants to retire
                            comfortably.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <!-- Risk Life Insurance -->
                <div
                    class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border-t-4 border-blue-600"
                >
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                        Perspective 2: Pure Life Insurance
                    </h3>
                    <span
                        class="inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded mb-4 font-bold"
                        >INCOME PROTECTION</span
                    >
                    <p class="text-sm mb-4">
                        <strong>Primary Goal:</strong> To pay your family if you die
                        prematurely.
                    </p>
                    <ul class="text-sm list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                        <li>
                            <strong>Mechanism:</strong> You pay a small fee. If you
                            die, it pays out huge. If you survive, you get nothing.
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Tax:</strong> NOT deductible (mostly).</li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Payout:</strong> Fixed sum (e.g., CHF 500,000)
                            regardless of what you paid in.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Use Case:</strong> Parents, Homeowners with mortgages.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 11.3 Can You Use Both? -->
            <div class="mb-16">
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                    The "Decoupling" Strategy
                </h3>
                <p>
                    Should you mix them? Traditional Swiss advisors often sell
                    "Mixed Life Insurance" (Gemischte Lebensversicherung) inside
                    a 3rd Pillar. This combines savings and death cover.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Modern Advice:</strong> Keep them separate.
                </p>
                <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6 rounded-xl mt-4">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                        Why Separate? (Decoupling)
                    </h4>
                    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-sm">
                        <li>
                            <strong>Flexibility:</strong> If you lose your job and
                            can't save, you can stop your 3rd Pillar bank payments.
                            But you keep paying the small fee for your pure Life Insurance
                            so your family stays protected.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Cost:</strong> Specialized products are cheaper.
                            A pure ETF 3a plan + a separate specialized Risk Policy
                            is usually CHEAPER than a bundled product.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Transparency:</strong> You see exactly what fee
                            goes to risk and what goes to savings.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 11.7 Decision Matrix -->
            <div class="mb-16">
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                    Decision Matrix
                </h3>
                <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                    <table
                        class="min-w-full text-sm border-collapse border border-gray-300"
                    >
                        <thead>
                            <tr class="bg-gray-800 text-white">
                                <th class="p-3 text-left border"
                                    >If you want...</th
                                >
                                <th class="p-3 text-left border"
                                    >Use This Product</th
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr class="bg-white">
                                <td class="p-3 border font-bold"
                                    >Tax Deduction</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-3 border text-red-600 font-bold"
                                    >Pillar 3a</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                                <td class="p-3 border font-bold"
                                    >Death Benefit (Lump Sum)</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-3 border text-blue-600 font-bold"
                                    >Risk Life Insurance</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-white">
                                <td class="p-3 border font-bold"
                                    >Investment Growth</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-3 border text-red-600 font-bold"
                                    >Pillar 3a (Bank/ETF)</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                                <td class="p-3 border font-bold"
                                    >Mortgage Protection</td
                                >
                                <td class="p-3 border text-blue-600 font-bold"
                                    >Risk Life Insurance</td
                                >
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- 11.8 Scenarios -->
            <div class="mb-16">
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                    Real World Scenarios
                </h3>

                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                    <div class="border p-4 rounded-lg">
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">
                            Young Professional (28, Single)
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                            <strong>Need:</strong> Wealth. <br />
                            <strong>Action:</strong> Max out Pillar 3a (Bank). Ignore
                            Life Insurance (no dependents).
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="border p-4 rounded-lg">
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">
                            New Parent (34, Married, Mortgage)
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                            <strong>Need:</strong> Protection & Wealth. <br />
                            <strong>Action:</strong> Max out Pillar 3a (Bank) for
                            retirement. Buy separate Death Risk Policy (CHF 300k coverage)
                            for ~CHF 200/year to cover the mortgage gap.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="border p-4 rounded-lg">
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">
                            Sole Breadwinner (45, 3 Kids)
                        </h4>
                        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                            <strong>Need:</strong> Maximum Security. <br />
                            <strong>Action:</strong> Max 3a. Heavily insured Risk
                            Policy (CHF 1M+) to replace income until kids are 25.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
